gh `MethodHandle` was not being attributed to the dynamic-access call site.\n- The generated helper emits a normal `invokestatic` to `OAuthScheme.class$(String)`, which should put the tracked frame directly on the stack and reach the `Class.forName(String)` call site.\n- Native Image dynamic class definition is handled by catching `Error` and accepting only `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)`, per repository rules.\n\nI did not run the tests.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_01956fb2de05879a016a0084e7057881a085509a072f8b91c3\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 542, "output": 545, "cacheRead": 38912, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 39999, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778418912568, "responseId": "resp_01956fb2de05879a016a0084e16f5481a0a7ae7b940a118476"}, "toolResults": []}
